
The max_iter parameter in logistic regression (and other iterative algorithms) sets the maximum number of iterations the algorithm will perform during the optimization process.
It controls how long the algorithm should keep iterating to find the best solution or converge to an optimal set of coefficients. 
The choice of max_iter can influence the model training process's convergence behavior and computational efficiency. 
In practice, it’s often helpful to start with a default value and adjust it based on the specific dataset and the observed convergence behavior.

